title: Former prosecutor, military vet: A look at Benghazi panel
text: Photo: Cliff Owen, AP FILE - In this Sept. 4, 2015, file photo, House Select Committee on Benghazi Chairman Trey Gowdy, R-S.C., talks with the media on Capitol Hill in Washington. Gowdy, 51, is a third-term tea partyer and former prosecutor from South Carolina. FILE - In this Sept. 4, 2015, file photo, House Select Committee on... WASHINGTON (AP) — When the House Select Committee on Benghazi holds its first public hearing in nearly 10 months, the spotlight will focus on a sole witness — Hillary Rodham Clinton, former first lady and senator, secretary of state and presidential contender.
